# Digital Asset Protection System - Implementation Walkthrough

## What was accomplished
I have built the complete microservices architecture as specified in your requirements. The system is designed to detect unauthorized usage of images and videos using cryptographic hashing and AI similarity.

### 1. Python Service (ML Engine)
- Created a robust FastAPI server handling hashing and embeddings.
- Implemented [models/cnn_model.py](file:///d:/Piracy_detection/digital-asset-protection/python-service/models/cnn_model.py) which uses a pretrained PyTorch ResNet18 model to generate 512-dimensional embeddings for images.
- Implemented [services/image_hash.py](file:///d:/Piracy_detection/digital-asset-protection/python-service/services/image_hash.py) and [services/video_hash.py](file:///d:/Piracy_detection/digital-asset-protection/python-service/services/video_hash.py) (using `imagehash` and OpenCV) to generate pHash, dHash, and frame-by-frame fingerprinting.
- Mathematical similarity logic added via `Hamming distance` and `Cosine similarity`.

### 2. Backend Node (Main Orchestrator)
- Created the Express.js backend with MongoDB integration (`mongoose`).
- [storageService.js](file:///d:/Piracy_detection/digital-asset-protection/backend-node/services/storageService.js) handles intermediate file uploads and local storage using `multer`.
- Integration with the Python service is fully handled in [pythonService.js](file:///d:/Piracy_detection/digital-asset-protection/backend-node/services/pythonService.js) using `axios` and `form-data`.
- API endpoints `POST /upload`, `GET /media`, `GET /violations`, and `POST /report` implemented in [mediaController.js](file:///d:/Piracy_detection/digital-asset-protection/backend-node/controllers/mediaController.js).

### 3. Scraper Service
- Scheduled a Node.js cron job to periodically scrape internet URLs.
- Implemented scraping mock logic using `axios` and temporary file downloads.
- [sendToPython.js](file:///d:/Piracy_detection/digital-asset-protection/scraper-node/services/sendToPython.js) forwards newly discovered media to the Python ML engine to compare against known reference media footprints.

### 4. React Frontend
- Built a modern, dark-themed UI with `Vite` and `React`.
- Configured dynamic routing using `react-router-dom`.
- Included three major components:
  1. **Upload**: Submits new media to the backend.
  2. **Dashboard**: Shows real-time monitoring stats and active scrapers.
  3. **ViolationCard**: Visually highlights unauthorized usage, returning the source URL and the model's confidence match percentage.

### 5. Dockerization & Structure
- Each service has its own [Dockerfile](file:///d:/Piracy_detection/digital-asset-protection/frontend/Dockerfile) optimized for its specific runtime (Python 3.10 and Node 18).
- A root [docker-compose.yml](file:///d:/Piracy_detection/digital-asset-protection/docker-compose.yml) orchestrates all services seamlessly alongside a MongoDB instance.
- Fully adhered to the strict folder structure requested.
- [docs/sample_requests.http](file:///d:/Piracy_detection/digital-asset-protection/docs/sample_requests.http) has been added for API interaction references.

